		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, a lot of arcade hardware at the time had sound made out of discrete components (instead of proper sound chips), and sine waves were pretty common. I suppose that the triangle wave is there to allow doing a (very) crude imitation of those sine waves, although in practice everybody would use the square waves anyway...

		

